From: Bottlerocket Team <bottlerocket@amazon.com>
Date: Fri, 07 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] openbsd-compat/xcrypt.c: guard crypt() call with HAVE_CRYPT

When building without libxcrypt (e.g. cross-compiling against a sysroot
that does not provide libcrypt), configure sets HAVE_CRYPT=0 but the
xcrypt() function still calls crypt() unconditionally in the else branch,
causing an undefined reference at link time.

Guard the crypt() call with #ifdef HAVE_CRYPT and return NULL otherwise,
matching the behaviour of the DES_crypt fallback path.

--- a/openbsd-compat/xcrypt.c
+++ b/openbsd-compat/xcrypt.c
@@ -100,7 +100,11 @@ xcrypt(const char *password, const char *salt)
 # elif defined(HAVE_SECUREWARE)
 	crypted = bigcrypt(password, salt);
 # else
+# ifdef HAVE_CRYPT
 	crypted = crypt(password, salt);
+# else
+	crypted = NULL;
+# endif
 #endif
 
 	return crypted;
